<BaseLayout title="Statement — Christopher Martino" current="statement"><section class="text-page"><p class="eyebrow">Statement</p><h1>The paintings begin with images that feel familiar but resist clear explanation.</h1><div class="prose"><p>I am interested in the unstable relationship between beauty and unease, and in the way ordinary spaces can hold traces of absence, repetition, and time.</p><p>Through editing, digital construction, models, and slow painting, I build images in which the process remains mostly invisible while the final surface retains a sense of uncertainty.</p></div></section></BaseLayout>
